(148, 2, '2019-03-04 17:17:27', '2019-03-04 17:17:27', '<h1>Complete Exterior Painting Job at the Buckhead house</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>We repaired holes and cracks in the drywall by placing the self-adhesive mesh patch over the hole. We used a drywall knife to cover the patch with lightweight joint compound in a crisscross pattern, and feathering the edges so it blends with the wall. We then let the patch dry.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We caulked all the joints between trim and wall surfaces to prevent penetration of moisture vapor into walls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then applied SuperPaint Interior Acrylic Latex by Sherwin-Williams. SuperPaint next generation delivers a smoother appearance, excellent hide, and helps make color changes more vibrant. Paint and primer in one for fast and easy application. Excellent hide and durability. Rich, beautiful appearance and a lasting finish.</p>', 'Beautiful Buckhead Exterior Painting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '131-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-04 17:17:27', '2019-03-04 17:17:27', '', 131, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/131-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(149, 2, '2019-03-04 17:22:41', '2019-03-04 17:22:41', '<p>A lot of prep work goes into creating the perfect base for an exterior painting job. To deliver the perfect results, we make sure to follow all the necessary steps in order to make sure that the paint applies evenly without any bubbles or other flaws.</p>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>First we scraped off the loose paint. We also scraped and sanded where we needed to feather edges for aesthetics, and create a good base for the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It\'s vital to seal any cracks, as well as the joints where one type of exterior material meets another. This includes: window frames, door frames, molding and fascia boards. We replaced fascia boards that showed signs of rotting. We then sanded wood trim and doors to ensure an ideal surface for painting. A good exterior paint was then applied to the exterior surfaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_7528-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Buford\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-169\" />\r\n\r\n<h2>Staining wood Shingles</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Staining cedar shingles not only enhances their beauty but also fortifies them against threats posed by the elements. To protect shingles we applied a penetrating stain. The stain soaks in and protects the wood from the weather, and it will prevent it from cracking, peeling, or chipping. We liberally brushed along the bottom edges of each course and then over the face of the shingles with a generous coat of stain. We started at the top courses and worked our way down.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Pergola Staining</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We checked the damaged boards that needed to be replaced. We pressure washed the pergola surface and allowed it to dry for at least 24 hours. We examined all the wood and made sure it was clean. We hand sanded areas that need additional attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then covered nearby areas of the house and make sure stain wouldn’t get on the siding or on the deck/patio. Using a spray shield or piece of cardboard will block any stain from getting to unwanted areas. Sprayed the stain in a consistent pattern and covered the surface well.</p>\r\n', 'Gorgeous Exterior Painting in Buford', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'buford', '', '', '2019-03-29 04:52:05', '2019-03-29 04:52:05', '', 0, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/?p=149', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(150, 2, '2019-03-04 17:22:41', '2019-03-04 17:22:41', '<p>First we scraped off the loose off and paint. We also scraped, sanded where we needed to feather edges for aesthetics, and paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It\'s vital to seal any cracks, as well as the joints where one type of exterior material meets another. This includes: window frames, door frames, molding and fascia boards. We replaced fascia boards that showed signs of rotting. We then sanded wood trim and doors to ensure an ideal surface for painting. A good exterior paint was then applied to the exterior surfaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Staining wood Shingles</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Staining cedar shingles not only enhances their beauty but also fortifies them against threats posed by the elements. To protect shingles we applied a penetrating stain. The stain soaks in and protects the wood from the weather, and it won’t crack, peel, or chip. We liberally brushed along the bottom edges of each course and then over the face of the shingles with a generous coat of stain. We started at the top courses and worked our way down.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Pergola Staining</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We checked the damaged boards that needed to be replaced. We pressure washed the pergola surface and allowed it to dry for at least 24 hours. We examined all the wood and made sure it was clean. We hand sanded areas that need additional attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then covered nearby areas of the house and make sure stain wouldn’t get on the siding or on the deck/patio. Using a spray shield or piece of cardboard will block any stain from getting to unwanted areas. Sprayed the stain in a consistent pattern and covered the surface well.</p>\r\n', 'Gorgeous Exterior Painting in Buford', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '149-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-04 17:22:41', '2019-03-04 17:22:41', '', 149, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/149-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(151, 2, '2019-03-04 17:28:16', '2019-03-04 17:28:16', '<p>We revived the brick exterior with a fresh coat of Sherwin-Williams Duration in Alpharetta. The Duration Home line is great for exterior surfaces because it is resistant to cracking and peeling. The paint itself provides thicker coating and it is self priming. Sherwin-Williams backs its Duration line with a limited lifetime warranty, which means you get the most bang for your buck guaranteed!</p> \r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Painted brick has a style all its own and is seen more and more as decorating trends shift.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We pressure washed to clean exterior brick. The primary point of the wash is to clear any dirt, grime, and loose paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the washing was completed, we allowed the brick plenty of time to fully dry. This took a few days because brick is a porous material that traps moisture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Removed all loose paint that was left behind on the brick face or else it will cause early chipping when you eventually apply your coat. We used a hand scraper to get the larger pieces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sanded the brick smooth using either a palm or circular sander. Then, repaired any missing and damaged mortar.\r\nAt the Alpharetta house we scraped and sanded any deteriorating surfaces. We then applied primer and sealed the brick with oil based zinsser cover stain primer.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_7100-1-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Alpharetta\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-165\" />\r\n\r\n<p>Caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush or vacuum.\r\nWhen choosing exterior house paint, Sherwin-Williams Duration is one of the best choices. Just look at the finished results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As we were finishing the brick paint job at the Alpharetta house the owners also asked us to stain their deck. This process included cleaning, pressure washing, they applying the stain.</p>\r\n', 'Exterior Painting in Alpharetta', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'alpharetta', '', '', '2019-03-21 22:27:10', '2019-03-21 22:27:10', '', 0, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/?p=151', 0, 'post', '', 0),
