(154, 2, '2019-03-04 17:30:55', '2019-03-04 17:30:55', '<p>Prime Painters gave the Duluth house a completely new look with Hardie Plank. Hardie Plank is definitely the way to go when it comes to an exterior overhaul because it looks just like wood—  delivering the same look that you love but retaining a more sturdy, concrete feel to the touch. Hardie Plank is also fire-resistant as well as insect and vermin resistant.</p>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Reglazing the windows</h2>\r\n<p>Glazing is the name of the hardened putty that creates a weathertight seal on the exterior of the window between the wood and the glass. For the glazing process all we need is a putty knife and a handful of well-kneaded glazing compound. Using the putty knife, we created perfect putty bevels. If the window is properly maintained, the glazing compound will last for many, many years.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_6036-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Duluth\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-163\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced existing rotted siding, with Hardie Plank vinyl siding, caulked edges and trims, afterwich the complete house and trim was painted with Sherwin-Williams Duration that has a lifetime warranty.</p>\r\n', 'Exterior Painting in Duluth', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'exterior-services-in-duluth', '', '', '2019-03-21 22:24:28', '2019-03-21 22:24:28', '', 0, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/?p=154', 0, 'post', '', 0);
</p>', 'Beautiful exterior painting in Johns Creek', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '127-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-07 21:04:48', '2019-03-07 21:04:48', '', 127, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/127-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(158, 2, '2019-03-07 21:05:15', '2019-03-07 21:05:15', '<h2>Refreshed the John’s Creek home with new brick paint</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We pressure washed the brick to clear away any loose dirt, paint, oils, or other debris to make sure that the new coat of paint will be easily applied.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once we finished pressure washing the brick, we gave it time to dry since brick can trap a lot of moisture into its pores. This took a few days to completely dry out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hand scraped the remaining loose dirt that clung to the brick surface so that there wouldn’t be any imperfections when we finally applied the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then sanded the brick smooth using a circular sander. Then, we repaired any missing and damaged mortar. We then applied primer to the brick so that the paint could be applied as smoothly as possible. We caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.\r\nBefore beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush. We chose Sherwin-Williams Resilience paint that comes with a lifetime warranty. The results are incredible!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced any wood that had rotted away and stained it so that it would elongate the life of the surface for years to come!</p>', 'Beautiful exterior painting in Johns Creek', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '127-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-07 21:05:15', '2019-03-07 21:05:15', '', 127, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/127-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
