(195, 2, '2019-03-21 18:21:19', '2019-03-21 18:21:19', 'Prime Painters gave the Duluth house a completely new look with Hardie Plank. Hardie Plank is definitely the way to go when it comes to an exterior overhaul because it looks just like wood—  delivering the same look that you love but retaining a more sturdy, concrete feel to the touch. Hardie Plank is also fire-resistant as well as insect and vermin resistant. \r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Reglazing the windows</h2>\r\n<p>Glazing is the name of the hardened putty that creates a weathertight seal on the exterior of the window between the wood and the glass. For the glazing process all we need is a putty knife and a handful of well-kneaded glazing compound. Using the putty knife, we created perfect putty bevels. If the window is properly maintained, the glazing compound will last for many, many years.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_6036-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Duluth\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-163\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced existing rotted siding, with Hardie Plank vinyl siding, caulked edges and trims, afterwich the complete house and trim was painted with Sherwin-Williams Duration that has a lifetime warranty.</p>\r\n', 'Exterior Painting in Duluth', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '154-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-21 18:21:19', '2019-03-21 18:21:19', '', 154, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/154-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(196, 2, '2019-03-21 19:15:57', '2019-03-21 19:15:57', '<p>We revived the brick exterior with a fresh coat of Sherwin-Williams Duration in Alpharetta. The Duration Home line is great for exterior surfaces because it is resistant to cracking and peeling. The paint itself provides thicker coating and it is self priming. Sherwin-Williams backs its Duration line with a limited lifetime warranty,  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Painted brick has a style all its own and is seen more and more as decorating trends shift.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We pressure washed to clean exterior brick. The primary point of the wash is to clear any dirt, grime, and loose paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the washing was completed, we allowed the brick plenty of time to fully dry. This took a few days because brick is a porous material that traps moisture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Removed all loose paint that was left behind on the brick face or else it will cause early chipping when you eventually apply your coat. We used a hand scraper to get the larger pieces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sanded the brick smooth using either a palm or circular sander. Then, repaired any missing and damaged mortar.\r\nAt the Alpharetta house we scraped and sanded any deteriorating surfaces. We then applied primer and sealed the brick with oil based zinsser cover stain primer.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_7100-1-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Alpharetta\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-165\" />\r\n\r\n<p>Caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush or vacuum.\r\nWhen choosing exterior house paint, Sherwin-Williams Duration is one of the best choices. Just look at the finished results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As we were finishing the brick paint job at the Alpharetta house the owners also asked us to stain their deck. This process included cleaning, pressure washing, they applying the stain.</p>\r\n', 'Exterior Painting in Alpharetta', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '151-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-21 19:15:57', '2019-03-21 19:15:57', '', 151, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/151-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(197, 2, '2019-03-21 19:31:12', '2019-03-21 19:31:12', '<p>We revived the brick exterior with a fresh coat of Sherwin-Williams Duration in Alpharetta. The Duration Home line is great for exterior surfaces because it is resistant to cracking and peeling. The paint itself provides thicker coating and it is self priming. Sherwin-Williams backs its Duration line with a limited lifetime warranty, which means you get the most bang for your buck guaranteed!</p>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Painted brick has a style all its own and is seen more and more as decorating trends shift.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We pressure washed to clean exterior brick. The primary point of the wash is to clear any dirt, grime, and loose paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the washing was completed, we allowed the brick plenty of time to fully dry. This took a few days because brick is a porous material that traps moisture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Removed all loose paint that was left behind on the brick face or else it will cause early chipping when you eventually apply your coat. We used a hand scraper to get the larger pieces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sanded the brick smooth using either a palm or circular sander. Then, repaired any missing and damaged mortar.\r\nAt the Alpharetta house we scraped and sanded any deteriorating surfaces. We then applied primer and sealed the brick with oil based zinsser cover stain primer.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_7100-1-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Alpharetta\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-165\" />\r\n\r\n<p>Caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush or vacuum.\r\nWhen choosing exterior house paint, Sherwin-Williams Duration is one of the best choices. Just look at the finished results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As we were finishing the brick paint job at the Alpharetta house the owners also asked us to stain their deck. This process included cleaning, pressure washing, they applying the stain.</p>\r\n', 'Exterior Painting in Alpharetta', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '151-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-21 19:31:12', '2019-03-21 19:31:12', '', 151, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/151-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
</p>', 'Beautiful exterior painting in Johns Creek', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '127-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-03-21 21:42:14', '2019-03-21 21:42:14', '', 127, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/127-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(208, 2, '2019-03-21 21:43:01', '2019-03-21 21:43:01', '<p>We gave the John\'s Creek home a brand new look with a fresh coat of exterior paint. Painting brick can give any home a facelift and breathe new life into it. We definitely think that this paint job made the John\'s Creek house the envy of all the neighbors. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>To start, we pressure washed the brick to clear away any loose dirt, paint, oils, or other debris to make sure that the new coat of paint will be easily applied. Once we finished pressure washing the brick, we gave it time to dry since brick can trap a lot of moisture into its pores. This took a few days to completely dry out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hand scraped the remaining loose dirt that clung to the brick surface so that there wouldn’t be any imperfections when we finally applied the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then sanded the brick smooth using a circular sander. Then, we repaired any missing and damaged mortar. We then applied primer to the brick so that the paint could be applied as smoothly as possible. We caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.\r\nBefore beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush. We chose Sherwin-Williams Resilience paint that comes with a lifetime warranty. The results are incredible!</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/IMG_4286-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-176\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced any wood that had rotted away and stained it so that it would elongate the life of the surface for years to come!</p>', 'Beautiful exterior painting in Johns Creek', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '127-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-21 21:43:01', '2019-03-21 21:43:01', '', 127, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/127-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(209, 2, '2019-03-21 21:43:19', '2019-03-21 21:43:19', '<p>We gave the John\'s Creek home a brand new look with a fresh coat of exterior paint. Painting brick can give any home a facelift and breathe new life into it. We definitely think that this paint job made the John\'s Creek house the envy of all the neighbors. </p><!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>To start, we pressure washed the brick to clear away any loose dirt, paint, oils, or other debris to make sure that the new coat of paint will be easily applied. Once we finished pressure washing the brick, we gave it time to dry since brick can trap a lot of moisture into its pores. This took a few days to completely dry out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hand scraped the remaining loose dirt that clung to the brick surface so that there wouldn’t be any imperfections when we finally applied the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then sanded the brick smooth using a circular sander. Then, we repaired any missing and damaged mortar. We then applied primer to the brick so that the paint could be applied as smoothly as possible. We caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.\r\nBefore beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush. We chose Sherwin-Williams Resilience paint that comes with a lifetime warranty. The results are incredible!</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/IMG_4286-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-176\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced any wood that had rotted away and stained it so that it would elongate the life of the surface for years to come!</p>', 'Beautiful exterior painting in Johns Creek', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '127-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-21 21:43:19', '2019-03-21 21:43:19', '', 127, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/127-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision',