(216, 2, '2019-03-29 04:49:36', '2019-03-29 04:49:36', '<p>We had the opportunity to do a complete interior painting job at the Buckhead house. There was quite a bit of work to be done since there were holes in the walls from nails and cracks from water damage, but our team easily got through the repairs so we could make the house look brand new again!</p>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We repaired holes and cracks in the drywall by placing the self-adhesive mesh patch over the hole. We used a drywall knife to cover the patch with lightweight joint compound in a crisscross pattern, and feathering the edges so it blends with the wall. We then let the patch dry.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/IMG_2548-1-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Buckhead Interior Painting\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-174\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We caulked all the joints between the trim and wall surfaces to prevent penetration of moisture vapor into walls. This also helps to keep the house well insulated to ensure that cold winter days are nice and toasty and that hot summer days are kept cool and refreshing indoors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then applied SuperPaint Interior Acrylic Latex by Sherwin-Williams. SuperPaint next generation delivers a smoother appearance, excellent hide, and helps make color changes more vibrant. Paint and primer in one for fast and easy application. Excellent hide and durability. Rich, beautiful appearance and a lasting finish.</p>', 'Beautiful Buckhead Interior Painting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '131-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-29 04:49:36', '2019-03-29 04:49:36', '', 131, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/131-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(217, 2, '2019-03-29 04:50:29', '2019-03-29 04:50:29', '<p>We gave the John\'s Creek home a brand new look with a fresh coat of exterior paint. Painting brick can give any home a facelift and breathe new life into it. We definitely think that this paint job made the John\'s Creek house the envy of all the neighbors. </p><!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>To start, we pressure washed the brick to clear away any loose dirt, paint, oils, or other debris to make sure that the new coat of paint will be easily applied. Once we finished pressure washing the brick, we gave it time to dry since brick can trap a lot of moisture into its pores. This took a few days to completely dry out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hand scraped the remaining loose dirt that clung to the brick surface so that there wouldn’t be any imperfections when we finally applied the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then sanded the brick smooth using a circular sander. Then, we repaired any missing and damaged mortar. We then applied primer to the brick so that the paint could be applied as smoothly as possible. We caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.\r\nBefore beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush. We chose Sherwin-Williams Resilience paint that comes with a lifetime warranty. The results are incredible!</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/IMG_4286-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"John\'s Creek Exterior Painting\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-176\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced any wood that had rotted away and stained it so that it would elongate the life of the surface for years to come!</p>', 'Beautiful Exterior Painting in Johns Creek', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '127-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-29 04:50:29', '2019-03-29 04:50:29', '', 127, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/127-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(218, 2, '2019-03-29 04:51:13', '2019-03-29 04:51:13', '<p>A lot of prep work goes into creating the perfect base for an exterior painting job. To deliver the perfect results, we make sure to follow all the necessary steps in order to make sure that the paint applies evenly without any bubbles or other flaws.</p>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>First we scraped off the loose paint. We also scraped and sanded where we needed to feather edges for aesthetics, and create a good base for the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It\'s vital to seal any cracks, as well as the joints where one type of exterior material meets another. This includes: window frames, door frames, molding and fascia boards. We replaced fascia boards that showed signs of rotting. We then sanded wood trim and doors to ensure an ideal surface for painting. A good exterior paint was then applied to the exterior surfaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_7528-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting in Buford\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-169\" />\r\n\r\n<h2>Staining wood Shingles</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Staining cedar shingles not only enhances their beauty but also fortifies them against threats posed by the elements. To protect shingles we applied a penetrating stain. The stain soaks in and protects the wood from the weather, and it will prevent it from cracking, peeling, or chipping. We liberally brushed along the bottom edges of each course and then over the face of the shingles with a generous coat of stain. We started at the top courses and worked our way down.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Pergola Staining</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We checked the damaged boards that needed to be replaced. We pressure washed the pergola surface and allowed it to dry for at least 24 hours. We examined all the wood and made sure it was clean. We hand sanded areas that need additional attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then covered nearby areas of the house and make sure stain wouldn’t get on the siding or on the deck/patio. Using a spray shield or piece of cardboard will block any stain from getting to unwanted areas. Sprayed the stain in a consistent pattern and covered the surface well.</p>\r\n', 'Gorgeous Exterior Painting in Buford', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '149-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-29 04:51:13', '2019-03-29 04:51:13', '', 149, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/149-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(219, 2, '2019-03-29 04:52:05', '2019-03-29 04:52:05', '<p>A lot of prep work goes into creating the perfect base for an exterior painting job. To deliver the perfect results, we make sure to follow all the necessary steps in order to make sure that the paint applies evenly without any bubbles or other flaws.</p>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>First we scraped off the loose paint. We also scraped and sanded where we needed to feather edges for aesthetics, and create a good base for the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It\'s vital to seal any cracks, as well as the joints where one type of exterior material meets another. This includes: window frames, door frames, molding and fascia boards. We replaced fascia boards that showed signs of rotting. We then sanded wood trim and doors to ensure an ideal surface for painting. A good exterior paint was then applied to the exterior surfaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_7528-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Buford\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-169\" />\r\n\r\n<h2>Staining wood Shingles</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Staining cedar shingles not only enhances their beauty but also fortifies them against threats posed by the elements. To protect shingles we applied a penetrating stain. The stain soaks in and protects the wood from the weather, and it will prevent it from cracking, peeling, or chipping. We liberally brushed along the bottom edges of each course and then over the face of the shingles with a generous coat of stain. We started at the top courses and worked our way down.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Pergola Staining</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We checked the damaged boards that needed to be replaced. We pressure washed the pergola surface and allowed it to dry for at least 24 hours. We examined all the wood and made sure it was clean. We hand sanded areas that need additional attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then covered nearby areas of the house and make sure stain wouldn’t get on the siding or on the deck/patio. Using a spray shield or piece of cardboard will block any stain from getting to unwanted areas. Sprayed the stain in a consistent pattern and covered the surface well.</p>\r\n', 'Gorgeous Exterior Painting in Buford', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '149-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-29 04:52:05', '2019-03-29 04:52:05', '', 149, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/149-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(220, 2, '2019-04-11 06:39:15', '2019-04-11 06:39:15', '<p>For this beautiful Lawrenceville house, we\'ve been asked to stain their pergola and deck, and then paint the trimmings as well of the wooden siding of their home. Prep work is key in all staining jobs and is essential because without it, wooden surfaces are susceptible to peeling, fading, and other things that will have you frustrated.</p><!--more-->\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<p>A wooden pergola can be a great way to reduce how much exposure to the sun your wooden deck gets. It offers some protection without completely covering the deck, making for a nice, shady retreat from the smoldering sun. The first thing we did was pressure wash the pergola in order to clear away any debris like moss, dirt, or other contaminants that would get in the way of a perfect finish. After letting the surface dry for a few days just to make sure that the stain would soak in nicely, we set to work covering everything in the vicinity to ensure that none of the stain would get on anything it wasn’t intended to. Lastly, we rolled the stain on, making sure that the surface was coated evenly. The finished result turned out great!</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/IMG_3010-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Lawrenceville\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-221\" />\r\n\r\n<p>The owners of the Lawrenceville house also asked us to stain their deck, so we used a similar approach to the pergola and pressure washed away any imperfections. We hand scraped away anything that remained just so be sure that the stain would set properly when the wood dried. Then, we stained the deck to nicely contrast the color of the siding on the house.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The siding of the house was painted to match the homeowner\'s vision and also to fit nicely in the neighborhood. We also carefully painted the trimming along the house to complete the exterior painting for the Lawrenceville house.\r\n\r\n', 'Amazing Exterior Painting in Lawrenceville', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'amazing-exterior-painting-in-lawrenceville', '', '', '2019-04-11 08:54:14', '2019-04-11 08:54:14', '', 0, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/?p=220', 0, 'post', '', 0),
