(127, 1, '2019-02-20 02:55:56', '2019-02-20 02:55:56', '<p>We gave the John\'s Creek home a brand new look with a fresh coat of exterior paint. Painting brick can give any home a facelift and breathe new life into it. We definitely think that this paint job made the John\'s Creek house the envy of all the neighbors. </p><!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>To start, we pressure washed the brick to clear away any loose dirt, paint, oils, or other debris to make sure that the new coat of paint will be easily applied. Once we finished pressure washing the brick, we gave it time to dry since brick can trap a lot of moisture into its pores. This took a few days to completely dry out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hand scraped the remaining loose dirt that clung to the brick surface so that there wouldn’t be any imperfections when we finally applied the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then sanded the brick smooth using a circular sander. Then, we repaired any missing and damaged mortar. We then applied primer to the brick so that the paint could be applied as smoothly as possible. We caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.\r\nBefore beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush. We chose Sherwin-Williams Resilience paint that comes with a lifetime warranty. The results are incredible!</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/IMG_4286-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"John\'s Creek Exterior Painting\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-176\" />\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced any wood that had rotted away and stained it so that it would elongate the life of the surface for years to come!INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(155, 2, '2019-03-04 17:30:55', '2019-03-04 17:30:55', 'Revitalized the Duluth house with Hardie Plank \r\n\r\n<h2>Reglazing the windows</h2>\r\n<p>Glazing is the name of the hardened putty that creates a weathertight seal on the exterior of the window between the wood and the glass. For the glazing process all we need is a putty knife and a handful of well-kneaded glazing compound. Using the putty knife, we created perfect putty bevels. If the window is properly maintained, the glazing compound will last for many, many years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Replaced existing rotted siding, with Hardie Plank vinyl siding, caulked edges and trims, afterwich the complete house and trim was painted with Sherwin-Williams Duration that has a lifetime warranty.</p>\r\n', 'Exterior Services in Duluth', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '154-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-04 17:30:55', '2019-03-04 17:30:55', '', 154, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/154-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(157, 2, '2019-03-07 21:04:48', '2019-03-07 21:04:48', '<h1>Refreshed the John’s Creek home with new brick paint</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>We pressure washed the brick to clear away any loose dirt, paint, oils, or other debris to make sure that the new coat of paint will be easily applied.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once we finished pressure washing the brick, we gave it time to dry since brick can trap a lot of moisture into its pores. This took a few days to completely dry out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We hand scraped the remaining loose dirt that clung to the brick surface so that there wouldn’t be any imperfections when we finally applied the paint.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then sanded the brick smooth using a circular sander. Then, we repaired any missing and damaged mortar. We then applied primer to the brick so that the paint could be applied as smoothly as possible. We caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.\r\nBefore beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush. We chose Sherwin-Williams Resilience paint that comes with a lifetime warranty. The results are incredible!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We also replaced any wood that had rotted away and stained it so that it would elongate the life of the surface for years to come!INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(168, 2, '2019-03-21 20:56:06', '2019-03-21 20:56:06', '<p>A lot of prep work goes into creating the perfect base for an exterior painting job. To deliver the perfect results, we make sure to follow all the necessary steps in order to make sure that the paint applies evFirst we scraped off the loose paint. We also scraped and sanded where we needed to feather edges for aesthetics, and create a good base for the paint.</p>\n\n<p>It\'s vital to seal any cracks, as well as the joints where one type of exterior material meets another. This includes: window frames, door frames, molding and fascia boards. We replaced fascia boards that showed signs of rotting. We then sanded wood trim and doors to ensure an ideal surface for painting. A good exterior paint was then applied to the exterior surfaces.</p>\n\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/IMG_7528-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-169\" />\n\n<h2>Staining wood Shingles</h2>\n\n<p>Staining cedar shingles not only enhances their beauty but also fortifies them against threats posed by the elements. To protect shingles we applied a penetrating stain. The stain soaks in and protects the wood from the weather, and it will prevent it from cracking, peeling, or chipping. We liberally brushed along the bottom edges of each course and then over the face of the shingles with a generous coat of stain. We started at the top courses and worked our way down.</p>\n\n<h2>Pergola Staining</h2>\n\n<p>We checked the damaged boards that needed to be replaced. We pressure washed the pergola surface and allowed it to dry for at least 24 hours. We examined all the wood and made sure it was clean. We hand sanded areas that need additional attention.</p>\n\n<p>We then covered nearby areas of the house and make sure stain wouldn’t get on the siding or on the deck/patio. Using a spray shield or piece of cardboard will block any stain from getting to unwanted areas. Sprayed the stain in a consistent pattern and covered the surface well.</p>\n', 'Gorgeous Exterior Painting in Buford', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '149-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-03-21 20:56:06', '2019-03-21 20:56:06', '', 149, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/uncategorized/149-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
