(207, 2, '2019-03-21 21:42:14', '2019-03-21 21:42:14', '<p>We gave the John\'s Creek home a brand new look with a fresh coat of exterior paint. Painting brick can give any home a facelift and breathe new life into it. We definit. </p>\n\n<p>We pressure washed the brick to clear away any loose dirt, paint, oils, or other debris to make sure that the new coat of paint will be easily applied.</p>\n\n<p>Once we finished pressure washing the brick, we gave it time to dry since brick can trap a lot of moisture into its pores. This took a few days to completely dry out.</p>\n\n<p>We hand scraped the remaining loose dirt that clung to the brick surface so that there wouldn’t be any imperfections when we finally applied the paint.</p>\n\n<p>We then sanded the brick smooth using a circular sander. Then, we repaired any missing and damaged mortar. We then applied primer to the brick so that the paint could be applied as smoothly as possible. We caulked any area that can let water in, even an opening as small as a 1/16 inch. This includes doors, windows, trim, and chimney caps.\nBefore beginning, we removed all the dust that’s come to rest on the brick face with a brush. We chose Sherwin-Williams Resilience paint that comes with a lifetime warranty. The results are incredible!</p>\n\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/IMG_4286-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-176\" />\n\n<p>We also replaced any wood that had rotted away and stained it so that it would elongate the life of the surface for years to come!INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(226, 2, '2019-04-11 07:33:21', '2019-04-11 07:33:21', '<p>We gave the Houchton house an exterior painting overhaul including a complete exterior repaint, caulking, rotten wood replacement, and deck staining. This beautiful house deserved attention to detail, so we made sure to pace ourselves in order to get everything ready for a perfect finish.</p> <!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>First, we assessed the integrity of the wood in the deck, quickly finding that it had been rotted and was in need of replacement. After we’d replaced the rotted wood, we caulked any cracks or places where the outside elements could damage the home from the outside, making sure to seal every one. Then, we hand scraped the surfaces of the house that we’d be painting in order to make a clean base for the paint to absorb into. Lastly, we used Sherwin-Williams Superpaint for the amazing final result.</p>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://primepaintersatlanta.com/current/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/IMG_3352_01-1-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"Exterior Painting Houchton\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-230\" />\r\n\r\n<p>Superpaint comes in handy against the elements; whether it’s storming and snowy or arid and dry, this paint applies smoothly and will resist fading, cracking, and peeling. Thanks to its advanced acrylic resin technology, this paint has  outstanding adhesion and color retention and it’s also dirt-resistant and mildew-resistant.</p>\r\n', 'Exterior Painting in Houchton', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'exterior-painting-in-houchton', '', '', '2019-04-11 08:54:58', '2019-04-11 08:54:58', '', 0, 'http://primepaintersatlanta.com/?p=226', 0, 'post', '', 0),
